==English==

===Noun===
'''anapest'''

an·a·pest (also anapaest, anapæst)

# A metrical [[foot]] consisting of three [[syllable]]s, two short and one long (e.g the word "[[velveteen]]").
# A fragment, phrase or line of poetry or verse using this meter; e.g. “Every Who down in Whoville liked Christmas a lot, but the Grinch, who lived just north of Whoville, did NOT!” ([http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dr_Seuss Dr Seuss] aka Theodor Geisel).


[Latin ''anapaestus'', from Greek ''anapaistos'': ''ana'' + ''paiein'', ''pais-'', to strike (an anapest is a reversed [[dactyl]])]

See ''pau(?)'' for possible [[Indo-European]] roots.

See [[anapestic]] (adj.)

